  "description": [
    "Peleliu Battle Ending MacArthur to Lead Philippines Liberation Bv FRANK TREMAINE United Press Wr Correspondent PEARL HARBOR Sept 19The bloody battle for Peleliu in the southern Palaus was believed near its culmination today as American forces wiped out more than half of the garrison seized nearly half of nearby Angaur Island and occupied tiny Ngarmoked Island off Peleliu These intensifield strikes carnet simultaneous with the opening of a new phase of the Southwest Pacific campaign by Gen MacArthur who will lead victorious Allied armies back to the Phillipines For the first time MacArthur sent carrierbased planes against Halama heras airdromes Saturday to prevent attacks on Americanheld Morotari island at the north end of the Hal mahera group and 250 miles south of the Phillipines The Jap Domei news agency re ported today that the Jap Navy had completed the evacuation of civilians from the Palau Islands Domei said the evacuation convoy included cruisers and destroyers Selection of MacArthur to command the invasion of the Phillipines was announced last night by Admiral Nunitz command in chief of the Pacific Fleet in a radio broadcast to the American Legion convention in Chicago 5495 JAPS KILLED The invasion of the Palaus 560 miles"
  ],
